cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.MA, cs.RO, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on using Wi-Fi ranging for positioning and improving network performance of mobile devices.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper mentions optimizing parameters in real-time, which could involve machine learning techniques.
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a possibility as the paper discusses pedestrian dead reckoning, which could involve multiple agents (i.e. pedestrians) interacting with each other.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is a possibility as the paper discusses using built-in sensors of mobile devices for positioning, which is similar to how robots use sensors for localization.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possibility as the paper discusses optimizing parameters in real-time to achieve robust performance, which is a common problem in control systems.
